    <string name="recenter_info_paragraph1">Some Snapdragon Spaces apps contain a digital laser that is
        controlled by the rotation of the companion controller. For these apps, occasionally the
        controller orientation may become misaligned with the digital laser, with the controller
        pointing in one direction with the laser pointing in another.
    </string>
    <string name="recenter_info_paragraph2">
        When this happens, you can re-orient the controller by performing the following steps:
    </string>
    <string name="recenter_info_paragraph3">
        1.	Click and hold the RECENTER Button which can be found at the bottom of Controller App
        while experiencing the offset inside the glasses application. This will freeze the digital laser in place.
    </string>
    <string name="recenter_info_paragraph4">
        2.	While holding the button down you can move and rotate the physical phone
        to attempt to align the rotation with the laser.
    </string>
    <string name="recenter_info_paragraph5">
        3.	Once lined up, release the RECENTER button to track to the new orientation setting.
    </string>
    <string name="recenter_info_paragraph6">
        4.	You may need to repeat this operation and experiment with different controller
        orientation offsets in order to achieve proper alignment.
    </string>
